<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,363]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differing from other Macropsini as follows: body form stout; clypellus dilated apically; striations on pronotum distinctly oblique; fore wing with 
<number box="[657,671,189,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
(in nominate subgenus 
<emphasis box="[944,958,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">P</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName box="[983,1081,189,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[983,1081,189,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Pedionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)) or 
<number box="[1140,1154,189,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
(in subgenus 
<emphasis box="[1315,1329,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">P</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName box="[1353,1416,189,213]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Thyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Pinophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1353,1416,189,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Thyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)) preapical cells, and veins usually marked with whitish spots; hind tibia with 
<number box="[1064,1078,226,250]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" value="8.0">8</number>
macrosetae on AD row; male pygofer tapering to point caudally, usually with small spinelike or acute tip; dorsal connective variously armed, usually with slender process twisted dorsally from bulbous base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
